  "summary": "While Mickey is away and Letitia Blacklock and Dora Bunner are in the village, Constable Fletcher investigates the house. He discovers that a door had been oiled to facilitate a silent exit from the drawing room after the lights were extinguished. Fletcher initially suspects an inhabitant, as he notes that the neighbors, the Simmons siblings, Philippa, Patrick, and Julia are all occupied or elsewhere. He searches the bedrooms of Philippa, Julia, Patrick, and Dora but finds nothing suspicious.\n\nDuring his investigation, Fletcher encounters Mrs. Sweetnam, who has entered through a side door to deliver quince to Miss Blacklock. She explains that the house is rarely locked because neighbors frequently come and go. Mrs. Sweetnam also mentions the \"Black Hand,\" prompting Fletcher to realize that an outsider could have easily entered the house while the residents were away, meaning he cannot rule out anyone present during the incident.\n\nElsewhere, a group consisting of Miss Muggleton, Miss Quickly, Miss Chipping, Miss Inchclyffe, and Muggeridge conducts a dramatic reenactment of a burglary to analyze the crime's logistics, specifically discussing how a thief might manage a door while using a flashlight and a revolver. Meanwhile, Colonel Eastbrooke informs his wife, Laura, that a German souvenir revolver, which was previously kept in his dressing room drawer, has gone missing.",
